## 3. Chapter Flow — KHÔNG Cố Định, Linh Hoạt

### Vấn đề

Plan trước nói "4 nhịp cố định" → **SAI, tôi đã verify lại tất cả 25 chapters và chỉnh sửa.**

### Thực tế từ 25 chapters (13 Genghis + 12 Caesar)

**5 kiểu mở chapter khác nhau:**

**Kiểu A: STANDARD** — "Level N, [label]. You are [age]."
```
Ch1: "Level one, the blood clot. You are born with..."
Ch3: "Level three, the first kill. You are 12."
Ch6: "Level six, the betrayal. You are 32."
```
→ Xuất hiện: ~50% chapters

**Kiểu B: CALLBACK** — 1-2 câu nối từ chapter trước, RỒI MỚI Level anchor
```
Ch4: "You will not hesitate again. Level four, the cage. You are 15."
Ch7: "He escapes into the steppe for now. Level seven, the name. You are 44."
```
→ Xuất hiện: ~25% chapters

**Kiểu C: THESIS** — Câu nhận định lớn, RỒI MỚI Level anchor
```
Ch9: "and you are about to aim it at the rest of the world. Level nine. The wall means nothing. You are 50."
Ch12: "Nothing in human history has ever moved this fast, this far, this completely. Level 12, the last campaign. You are 63."
```
→ Xuất hiện: ~15% chapters

**Kiểu D: ATMOSPHERE** — Bối cảnh không gian/thời gian TRƯỚC Level anchor
```
Ch10 (Reckoning): "You sit in the empty throne room and feel nothing but the pull of the next direction. There is still so much further to go. Level 10, the reckoning. You are 55."
Ch11 (Erasing): "The Khwarazmian Empire has stood for four centuries. In your mind, it is already ash. Level 11. The flood. You are 56."
```
→ Xuất hiện: ~8% chapters

**Kiểu E: COLD OPEN** — Không có "Level" word, nhảy thẳng vào
```
Caesar Ch11: "The ides. You are still 55. March 15th, 44 BC."
Caesar Ch4: "You always mean what you say. Level four, the weeping general."
```
→ Xuất hiện: ~2-5% chapters (hiếm, dùng cho high-impact moments)

### Writer prompt sẽ dạy MENU, không phải FORMULA

Thay vì rule cứng "mở bằng Level N + age", writer prompt sẽ:
- Liệt kê 5 kiểu opening làm **menu**
- Yêu cầu: **KHÔNG LẶP** kiểu mở 3 chapters liên tiếp
- Yêu cầu: Level anchor + age PHẢI xuất hiện trong 2 câu đầu (bất kể kiểu nào)
- Khuyến khích: chapters càng về sau càng dùng Callback/Thesis/Atmosphere nhiều hơn

### Sentence rhythm — KHÔNG cố định

Plan trước nói "SHORT-SHORT-LONG lặp lại" → **SAI — thực tế có 4 patterns xen kẽ:**

**Pattern 1: STACCATO** (hành động nhanh)
```
"Clean. Final. Your mother weeps for days."
"You refuse. You ride out."
```

**Pattern 2: WAVE** (build → release)
```
"A merchant convoy of 450 men, traveling under your banner and your protection, 
is massacred at a western border by a governor who wanted their goods."
→ Câu dài build tension, rồi câu ngắn release
```

**Pattern 3: BUILD** (ngắn → dài dần → climax)
```
"Cities that open their gates are absorbed. Cities that resist are not simply 
defeated. They are erased. Your engineers divert an entire river to wash away 
one city's ruins. So completely there is no foundation left to rebuild on."
```

**Pattern 4: STILLNESS** (câu dài, chậm, nặng)
```
"You look at the horizon. No satisfaction, only distance. The steppe ends 
somewhere out there. You have already decided where you are going next."
```

Writer prompt sẽ:
- Mô tả cả 4 patterns
- Yêu cầu: mỗi chapter dùng ít nhất 2 patterns khác nhau
- CẤM: dùng cùng 1 pattern cho toàn bộ chapter

